# Duro Design System — Cursor Rules

## Critical: react-strict-dom

All elements MUST use `html.*` from react-strict-dom. Never use raw HTML tags.

```tsx
import {css, html} from 'react-strict-dom'
<html.div style={styles.container}>...</html.div>  // ✅
<div className="container">...</div>               // ❌
```

## Critical: Token imports

Use deep imports. Barrel imports break StyleX babel plugin.

```tsx
import {colors} from '@duro-app/tokens/tokens/colors.css'     // ✅
import {spacing} from '@duro-app/tokens/tokens/spacing.css'   // ✅
import {colors} from '@duro-app/tokens'                        // ❌
```

## Layout Components

| Need | Component |
|---|---|
| Vertical stack | `Stack` |
| Horizontal, no wrap | `Inline` |
| Horizontal, wraps | `Cluster` |
| Multi-column grid | `Grid` |
| Full page | `PageShell` |

## Compound Components (Root required, throws without)

- `Select`: Root > Trigger + Popup > Item
- `Menu`: Root > Trigger + Popup > Item | LinkItem
- `Tabs`: Root > List > Tab + Panel
- `Table`: Root > Header + Body > Row > HeaderCell | Cell
- `Tooltip`: Root > Trigger
- `SideNav`: Root > Group > Item
- `ScrollArea`: Root > Viewport > Content + Scrollbar > Thumb

## Form Pattern

```tsx
import {Schema} from 'effect'
import {Form, Field, Input, Fieldset, Button} from '@duro-app/ui'

const MySchema = Schema.Struct({
  email: Schema.String.pipe(Schema.pattern(/^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$/, {message: () => 'Invalid'})),
})

<Form schema={MySchema} defaultValues={{email: ''}} onSubmit={handleSubmit}>
  {({formState}) => (
    <Fieldset.Root gap="md">
      <Field.Root name="email">
        <Field.Label>Email</Field.Label>
        <Input type="email" />
        <Field.Error />
      </Field.Root>
      <Button type="submit" disabled={!formState.isValid}>Submit</Button>
    </Fieldset.Root>
  )}
</Form>
```

Field.Root also works standalone (without Form) — pass `invalid` prop manually.

## Styling

```tsx
const styles = css.create({
  container: {
    padding: spacing.md,
    backgroundColor: colors.bgCard,
  },
})
<html.div style={[styles.container, isActive && styles.active]}>
```

## Spacing Scale

xs=4px, sm=8px, ms=12px, md=16px, lg=24px, xl=32px, xxl=48px, xxxl=64px

## Button Variants

`primary` (default), `secondary`, `inverseSecondary`, `link`, `danger`

Use `LinkButton` (not Button) for navigation — it renders an `<a>` tag.

## Typography

Use `Heading` (level 1-6) for headings, `Text` for body/labels.
Text variants: `bodySm`, `bodyMd`, `bodyLg`, `caption`, `label`, `code`, `overline`

For the full reference, see CLAUDE.md in the project root.
